comment_text: Baimbale (bamboo shoot), kummu(mushroom), therme thoppu(fiddle head ferns), kaad maange (wild mango) are few delicacies of Kodavas. It was an important part of our lives while growing up in Coorg to wake up early and go foraging for these things. When everyone runs inside during storm, we ran out to the forests to pick up wild mangoes which fell from the trees due to high winds. Those mangoes have very unique aroma and taste. We make gravy and raitha with those. Gulshan was my husband's neighbour in BEL and lovely to see you both. Very nice of him to give a glimpse of kodava cuisine‚ù§Ô∏è

comment_text: Rosogolla is not supposed to be spongy. It was made so for the commercial market so that it can withstand the shocks while in the can. My entire life i had rosogolla which were soft , slightly warm and melts in the mouth with a simple bite. That jiggly softness with mild taste of chena just makes me nostalgic. I remember their were rosogolla karigars who used to come to my nanny‚Äôs and make those buckets and buckets of rosogollas for every celebration or function.
